                    <msContents>
                        <summary>The romance of <title>Yūsuf va Zulaykhā</title>, a mystical love story inspired by the biblical tale of Joseph
                            and Potiphar's wife, comprises the fifth book of the <title>Haft Awrang</title> (Seven Thrones) by 
                            <persName key="person_90042997" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90042997/" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Nūr al-Dīn Al-Raḥmān Ibn Aḥmad ibn
                            Muḥammmad Jāmī (d. 1492)</persName>. A scribe named <persName role="scr">ʿAlī Akbar valad-i Muḥammad Muḥsin Zakī al-Ḥusaynī</persName> 
                            completed this manuscript at the fortress at <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7549668" key="place_7549668">Bidar</placeName> 
                            on <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1786-10-31">8 Muḥarram 1201 AH (31 Oct.
                                1786 CE)</date>.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_980-item1">
                            <author key="person_90042997" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90042997/">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Jāmī, 1414-1492</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">جامی</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20148" change="#ids-cleanup">Yūsuf va Zulaykhā</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20148" change="#ids-cleanup">يوسف و زليخا</title>
                                                      <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
